# Patch 0027 — Complete the Kavacha command registry: domain-grouped palette
# display + the plugin/marketplace surface (ROADMAP Phase 3 "Command registry";
# PLATFORM_PLAN.md § "Command registry").
#
# The registry infrastructure landed in patch 0018 and every shipped Kavacha
# feature already registers a command (0018/0020/0021/0022/0023/0024/0025).
# 0018 explicitly deferred two things and named the registry as "the surface
# plugins extend" without yet building that surface; 0027 finishes both:
#
#   1. Domain-grouped display. all() now returns commands clustered by a
#      declared domain order (KavachaCommandDomainOrder), so related commands
#      sit together in Cmd+K instead of interleaving. Each palette payload also
#      carries a localized `group` label (kavacha-command-domain-*), ready for a
#      grouped result renderer. A reserved AUTOMATION domain is added for the
#      Phase 7 workflow commands (and for plugins) so the ordering already knows
#      where they go.
#
#   2. The plugin/marketplace surface. register() gains source attribution +
#      validation + duplicate rejection; unregister()/unregisterBySource() let a
#      disabled plugin or uninstalled marketplace component drop every command it
#      added, and a new onUnregister sink removes those from the LIVE palette
#      (mirroring the existing onRegister add). getByDomain()/has()/domainLabel()
#      and a KavachaCommandCapability enum round out the API the marketplace
#      (patch 0028) and the SDK + permission model (patch 0029) build on.
#
# No new feature commands and no engine files — this completes the registry
# mechanism itself. Restore-archived-space stays menu-driven (0018's note: it
# needs a picker and has no clean single-call opener).
#
# NOT BUILD-VERIFIED: authored without a local Zen checkout; the
# KavachaCommandRegistry.sys.mjs rewrite is exact (its pre-image blob matches the
# post-0025 tree) but the ZenUBGlobalActions.sys.mjs and .ftl hunks are
# reconstructed against the post-0026 tree. Run `git -C browser/zen-upstream
# apply --check` + a Marionette pass (open Cmd+K, confirm commands cluster by
# domain; register/unregister a runtime command and watch the palette) before
# marking the ROADMAP item verified. Touches: zen-command-palette.ftl,
# KavachaCommandRegistry.sys.mjs, ZenUBGlobalActions.sys.mjs. Applies on top of
# 0026.
